<p><strong>Skills</strong> Arcana +3, Perception +3, Intimidation +5</p>

<p><strong>Damage Immunities</strong> cold</p>

<p><strong>Languages</strong> Common</p>

<p><strong>Challenge</strong> 3 (700 XP)</p>

<p><strong><em>Chilling Mist.</em></strong> While it is alive, the one-eyed shiver projects an aura of cold mist within 10 feet of itself. If the one-eyed shiver deals damage to a creature in this area, the creature also takes 5 (1d10) cold damage.</p>

<p><strong><em>Spellcasting.</em></strong> The one-eyed shiver is a 5th-level spellcaster. Its spellcasting ability is Charisma (spell save DC 13, +5 to hit with spell attacks). It knows the following sorcerer spells:</p>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p>Cantrips (at will): chill touch, mage hand</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>1st level (4 slots): fog cloud, mage armor, thunderwave</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>2nd level (3 slots): mirror image, misty step</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>3rd level (2 slots): fear</p>
  </li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Actions</strong></p>

<p><strong><em>Dagger.</em></strong> Melee Weapon Attack: +4 to hit, reach 5 ft. or range 20/60 ft., one target. Hit: 4 (1d4 + 2) piercing damage.</p>

<p><strong><em>Eye of Frost.</em></strong> The one-eyed shiver casts ray of frost from its missing eye. If it hits, the target is also restrained. A target restrained in this way can end the condition by using an action, succeeding on a DC 13 Strength check.</p>

